<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3075] Reliable delete table</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3075</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;New master makes it so enable/disable show as near instantaneous but behind the scenes we still have to do the region close/opens.  These can take time.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3063&quot; title=&quot;TestThriftServer failing in TRUNK&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3063&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3063&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; adds into the disable table handler a wait on regions leaving regions in transition but, what if the user did enable/disable/enable/disable then delete.  Turns out we don&apos;t do this well.  It confuses.  See the TestThriftServer where we&apos;ve disabled such a sequence.  This issue is about working on making delete work better; e.g. why bother closing stuff if we&apos;re going to delete it &amp;#8212; just abort the tables regions and save all the flushing, etc., that slows the close-before-delete.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
